d.en: a large bomb (500 to 2,000 pounds that is 50% explosive) whose explosion creates a blast and whose metal casing creates some fragmentation effect
d.ro: bombă mare (250-1000 kg, cu 50% explozibil), a cărei explozie creează o flacără
d.ja: 爆発が爆発を引き起こす、そして、金属ケースが若干の断片化効果をつくる大きな爆弾（50%爆発的である500〜2,000ポンド）

d.en: a bomb that has a detonating mechanism that can be set to go off at a particular time
d.de: eine Bombe mit einem Sprengmechanismus, der so eingestellt werden kann, dass sie zu einem bestimmten Zeitpunkt hochgeht
d.ja: ある時刻に爆発するようにセットできる爆破装置をもつ爆弾

d.en: a bomb placed in a car and wired to explode when the ignition is started or by remote control or by a timing device
d.ro: Automobil care explodează când este făcut contactul la motor
d.ja: 点火がスタートしたり、あるいは遠隔操作、時限装置により、爆発するように配線され自動車に仕掛けられる爆弾

d.en: bomb consisting of a canister that is dropped from a plane and that opens to release a cluster of bomblets (usually fragmentation bombs) over a wide area
d.ja: 航空機から落とされ広域に渡って一束の破砕爆弾が解放されるべく開くような散弾

d.en: (military) bomb consisting of an explosive projectile filled with a toxic gas that is released when the bomb explodes
d.ja: 爆弾が爆発すると開放される有毒ガスを詰めた爆弾発射体

d.en: a bomb with only 10 to 20 per cent explosive and the remainder consisting of casings designed to break into many small high-velocity fragments; most effective against troops and vehicles
d.da: mine som er konstrueret med henblik på at dræbe el…
d.ro: Bombă care conține bile sau cuie pentru a răni sau ucide cât mai mulți oameni
d.ja: 小さな高速の断片を破壊する外皮からなる10から20パーセントの爆薬と残留物; 軍隊および車に対して最も有効

d.en: a bomb that is designed to start fires; is most effective against flammable targets (such as fuel)
d.ro: Bombă menită a provoca incendii
d.ja: 火災を生じさせるよう考案された爆弾; 可燃性ターゲットに対して最も効果的（燃料のような）
